Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of adaptively learning a probability distribution's mode using oracle queries. This problem is related to machine learning and statistics, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves analyzing the query complexity of the algorithms, which is related to information theory, covered by the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of querying indices and comparing samples, which is related to data structures and algorithms, covered by the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
